GUGULETHU - Police Minister Bheki Cele says fighting crime requires a joint effort between communities and police. He addressed Gugulethu and Nyanga residents on Tuesday about increasing incidents of violent crime and mass shootings in these areas. Residents say police stations need more vehicles and more dedicated officers. WATCH:Â Cele lashes out at Action Society Meanwhile, Action Society wants Cele fired and is accusing him of politicising crime. The Minister has promised to host an Imbizo with other stakeholders including the Justice Department to address the rampant crime in the Western Cape. * eNCA's Nobesuthu Hejana reports.